	<a name="newsitem1034741015,99291,"></a><br><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0000EE">Work work... job ... NOT DONE</font><br><small><font size="1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0000EE">Tuesday, October 15, 2002</font></small><br><br><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font color="#000000">Work sux?!<br><br>Some people work from 9 to 5<br>Some people work from Noon to 8<br>Some people work from Midnight to 9<br>Heck, some people even work from 7 to 11 and,<br>Hell, some people work from 7 to 3 and home is only for shower and change of clothing<br><br>Some people make 300 per week<br>Some people make 500 per week<br>Some people make 1000 per week<br>Some people make 1500 per week, and<br>Some people try to get as much as possible under the table<br><br>Some people work to bring food to the dinner table<br>Some people work to satisfy their parents' expectation<br>Some people work to keep themselves out of trouble<br>Some people work to make sure their children will not need to work as hard as they do now, and<br>Some people will tell you that they don't know why they are working<br><br>Some people love their jobs<br>Some people can live with their jobs<br>Some people have to stay in the jobs for whatever the reasons<br>Some people hate their jobs, and<br>Some people don't know what to do with their jobs<br><br>So what do you do with your job?<br>So how do you like your job?<br>So can you make a living with your job?<br>So are you really doing your best at your job?<br>Or are you just trying to get by at your job?<br><br>While I am desperately looking for a job<br><br><br><br></p></font></font><a name="newsitem1034735572,82873,"></a><br><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0000EE">Shredded LIVE on 10-12-02</font><br><br><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font color="#000000"><img src="http://www.geocities.com/shreddednyc/shredded2.gif"><br><br>from left to right, Albert, Mike, Ting (back) Adam<br><br>ps. that female-looking figure was there b/c the owner of the place put it. NOT BY US lol</p></font></font><a name="newsitem1033506844,89974,"></a><br><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0000EE"></font><br><small><font size="1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0000EE">Tuesday, October 1, 2002</font></small><br><br><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font color="#000000">Leave Me Alone<br><br><br>&#25105;&#30693;&#36947;&#25105;&#19981;&#26159;&#20160;&#40636; <br>&#20063;&#30693;&#36947;&#33258;&#24049;&#27794;&#19977;&#23567;&#36335;&#29992;<br>&#25105;&#23565;&#20320;&#22519;&#24544;<br>&#20320;&#21371;&#25226;&#25105;&#30070;&#22900;&#38584;&#20351;&#29992;<br>&#20170;&#22825;&#26202;&#19978;&#25105;&#19979;&#27770;&#24515;&#19981;&#20877;&#25509;&#21463;<br>&#25343;&#36215;&#34892;&#26446;&#21521;&#22806;&#36208;&#25105;&#19981;&#26371;&#22238;&#38957; <br><br>&#25105;&#24050;&#28961;&#25152;&#27714; &#21482;&#24819;&#35201;&#25214;&#21040;&#33258;&#24049;&#30340;&#22825;&#31354;<br>&#25105;&#27794;&#26377;&#25226;&#25569; &#19968;&#20491;&#20154;&#33021;&#22816;&#36942;&#30340;&#28961;&#24616;&#28961;&#24962;<br>&#20294;&#26159;&#25105;&#30693;&#36947;&#36889;&#26159;&#25105;&#33258;&#24049;&#30340;&#25104;&#23601;<br>&#19978;&#24202;&#24460;&#25105;&#19981;&#26371;&#26377;&#25152;&#24460;&#24724;&#32780;&#28961;&#27861;&#20837;&#22818;<br><br><br>**Leave me alone<br>&#25105;&#19981;&#24819;&#35201;&#20877;&#32893;&#20320;&#22312;&#37027;&#32993;&#35498;<br>&#25105;&#30693;&#36947;&#25105;&#21487;&#20197;&#33258;&#24049;&#22533;&#24375;&#30340;&#21521;&#21069;&#36208;<br>Just Leave me alone<br>I don't want to be bothered anymore**<br>&#25105;&#24050;&#21463;&#22816; and I don't want it anymore<br>Leave me alone<br><br>repeat **<br><br>&#26377;&#19968;&#22825;&#20320;&#23559;&#26371;&#24460;&#24724;&#30070;&#21021;&#27794;&#26377;&#29645;&#24796;&#25105;<br>&#25105;&#26089;&#24050;&#36960;&#36208;<br><br>Leave me alone</p></font></font><a name="newsitem1033285148,5662,"></a><br><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0000EE">ROAD RAGE!</font><br><small><font size="1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0000EE">Sunday, September 29, 2002</font></small><br><br><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font color="#000000">"Rock on!"<br><br>"Yo! WTF is this? If you can't drive, stay home!"<br><br>"Let'S MOVE IT you f*cking rubberneckers!"<br><br>"Damn it! If you gonna make a left/right turn, get your F*cking signal on!"<br><br>"Don't you DARE moving! It's red god damn it!"<br><br>(Opening door after stopping b/c some jerk knocked my door for no reason on 57st. and Lextinton. Pointing at him) YO F*CK YOU! (530pm)<br><br>Steps<br>1. "What the F*ck is your problem!"<br>2. (lowering shotgun's window)<br>3. (threw chinese food in a take-out box at the car right of my car)<br>4. (the box broke open as it hit the half-lowered driver window)<br>5. (the ass had a chinese meal "to-go") <--- LIE East on the split between express line and local line to Queens Blvd.<br>STorY on this one will be out soon. I dont do this for no reason lol!<br><br><br>My only regret:<br><br>Wasn't old, bold, mature, and crazy enough to run a freaking POS in his 89 Corola on Grand Central Parkway with my Jeep on my 21st B-day after he hit the break really hard on me b/c he thought i was too slow on the left line!<br><br>ARGH!!!!!!<br><br></p></font></font><a name="newsitem1033093251,19433,"></a><br><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0000EE">translation for "The one who doesn't realize"</font><br><small><font size="1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0000EE">Thursday, September 26, 2002</font></small><br><br><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font color="#000000">female: <br><br>She always gets up before you do. Breakfast is always ready when you are set for work.<br><br>But you never treasure her, not even a simple "Thank you" for her.<br><br>She always cares about you. She even worries about you being hungry at work.<br><br>Do you know, she is so good to you. Washing clothes during the day and making dinner at night.<br>Do you know, she is so good to you. Never spend much, and never ask you for any jewelary. Do you know?<br><br>Male:<br> <br>He never needs you to wake him up at 6am. While you are still at sleep he has gone to work.<br><br>But you never treasure him. After a busy day of work, you dare to give him only bread for dinner.<br><br>He always cares about you.  He worries about not providing you enough than other women.<br><br>Do you know, he is so good to you. From 9 to 5 he works, and he takes care of the baby when he is back.<br>Do you know, he is so good to you. He works hard, and he always turn in all of his salary. Do you know?<br><br>Male:<br>You don't realize how lucky you are<br><br>Female:<br>Your brain is as stupid as a pig's<br><br>Male: <br>OH! Pigs are not stupid and pigs are not slow<br><br>Female:<br>Fine! Pigs are not stupid and pigs are not slow<br><br>Male:<br>So! I am not stupid and I am not slow<br><br>Female:<br>No! You are so stupid and slow that you are like made out of wood<br><br>Female:<br><br>Do you know, she is so good to you. You never have to worry b/c she takes care of everything at home.<br><br>Male:<br><br>Do you know, he is so good to you. The only reason he works extra hours is b/c he wants to save up and take you on a vacation.<br><br>Together:<br><br>Do you know, he/she is so good to you.  He/She just want to stay with you till the end of the time.<br><br>Do you know, he/she is so good to you. Hope you can at least treat him/her 1/10000 of how he/she treat you.<br><br>Do you know?<br><br>Male:<br><br>You slowly food!<br><br>Female:<br><br>Do you know? </p></font></font><a name="newsitem1032931293,15628,"></a><br><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0000EE">&#20154;&#22312;&#31119;&#20013;&#19981;&#30693;&#31119;</font><br><small><font size="1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0000EE">Tuesday, September 24, 2002</font></small><br><br><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font color="#000000">April, 1998<br><br><br>&#22899;:  <br><br>&#27599;&#22825;&#37117;&#19968;&#27171; &#22905;&#36215;&#24471;&#27604;&#20320;&#26089;  &#22312;&#20320;&#20986;&#38272;&#30340;&#26178;&#20505; &#26089;&#39184;&#24050;&#28310;&#20633;&#22909;<br>&#20294;&#26159;&#20320;&#21371;&#24478; &#19981;&#29645;&#24796;&#22905;&#30340;&#22909;  &#22905;&#36899;&#35442;&#32893;&#21040;&#30340;&#35613;&#35613;&#37117;&#27794;&#26377;&#20139;&#21463;&#21040;<br>&#22905;&#30340;&#24515; &#27704;&#36960;&#22312;&#28858;&#20320;&#25805;&#21214;  &#23601;&#24597;&#20320; &#32922;&#23376;&#22312;&#20844;&#21496;&#35041;&#21617;&#21617;&#21483;<br><br>&#20320;&#30693;&#19981;&#30693;&#36947; &#22905;&#23565;&#20320;&#22810;&#40636;&#22909; &#30333;&#22825;&#27927;&#34915; &#26202;&#19978;&#36996;&#35201;&#24171;&#20320;&#19979;&#27700;&#39171;<br>&#20320;&#30693;&#19981;&#30693;&#36947; &#22905;&#23565;&#20320;&#22810;&#40636;&#22909; &#30465;&#21507;&#27298;&#29992; &#24478;&#20358;&#19981;&#26366;&#21521;&#20320;&#35201;&#29664;&#23542;<br>&#20320;&#30693;&#19981;&#30693;&#36947;<br><br>&#30007;:  <br><br>&#20845;&#40670;&#37912;&#36215;&#24202; &#20182;&#24478;&#19981;&#35201;&#22963;&#21483; &#22312;&#22963;&#29087;&#30561;&#30340;&#26178;&#20505; &#20182;&#26089;&#20197;&#24448;&#20844;&#21496;&#36305;<br>&#20294;&#26159;&#22963;&#21371;&#24478; &#19981;&#29645;&#24796;&#20182;&#30340;&#22909; &#20182;&#22312;&#22806;&#24537;&#20102;&#19968;&#22825;&#24460; &#26202;&#39184;&#31455;&#28982;&#21482;&#26159;&#40629;&#21253;<br>&#20182;&#30340;&#24515; &#27704;&#36960;&#22312;&#28858;&#22963;&#25805;&#21214; &#23601;&#24597;&#20320; &#27794;&#26377;&#27604;&#21029;&#20154;&#36942;&#30340;&#22909;<br><br>&#22963;&#30693;&#19981;&#30693;&#36947; &#20182;&#23565;&#